column1: Inside FERC's Gas Market Report monthly bidweek price file.
When done, e-mail to BOTH kdool@mh.com AND mhenergy@yahoo.com
or fax to 202-383-2109, attention: Kelley Doolan
Prices must be sent to INSIDE FERC by 3:30 pm EASTERN TIME on the last business day of the month or
they might not be included.  If you have problems, call 202-383-2145 (Kelley Doolan)
SURVEY / WORKBOOK  NOTES:
* The essential fields to fill out below are the price, volume, date and price source (your company name) fields.
* Add the specific pipeline names and delivery points in column A as you go.
* We round the volumes to the nearest thousand, and truncate the last three zeros,
ie, 15,320 MMBtu/day is entered as just 15; likewise, 3,000 MMBtu/day, as 3, etc.
* Only report FIXED-PRICED,  BASELOAD DEALS negotiated during BIDWEEK. NO EFPs please, or basis deals.
* In the last two columns on the right, please report a low and a high for BASIS DEALS during BIDWEEK
at each pricing point. The basis should be reported as plus or minus values to the last day NYMEX
Henry Hub Settlement price, ie., minus a half cents is -0.05, etc.
* Please do not change the format of the file, and do not put formulas in the cells, just values.
Thank you for participating, Kelley Doolan.
example:
ANR Louisiana
ANR Louisiana
NGPL LA Pool
NGPL TXOK
TRKL ELA
